<title>USA: MSRB concerned about pay-to-play loopholes - RFTV.</title>
<headline>MSRB concerned about pay-to-play loopholes - RFTV.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>U.S. municipal bond regulators are disturbed by reports that bond dealers are using loopholes to get around campaign finance restrictions and will review the allegations, a regulator said Thursday.</p>
<p>&quot;It is of concern to the board that we are hearing reports...that the politicians are approaching the dealers and asking for money no longer for their campaigns, but for party contributions as a condition for doing business,&quot; Christopher Taylor, executive director of the Municipal Securities Rulemaking Board, told RFTV in an interview. &quot;This is very disturbing it is a variant of pay-to-play.&quot;</p>
</text>
